	<div class="part">
		<div class="title">
			<h2><span class="underscore">Git</span>, the VCS</h2>
			<p>We used to work with version control system (VCS), named SVN, if you remember, and Git is a VCS, and is more powerful than SVN</p>
		</div><!-- END .title -->
		<div class="content">
			<h2>The goals</h2>
			<ol>
				<li><span class="italic">Register & setup a Github account</span>
					<blockquote>
						<p>Here, at <a href="http://github.com">http://github.com.</a></p>
						<p>Make sure that you have the appropriate tool for working with Github, too.</p>
					</blockquote>
				</li>
				
				<li><span class="italic">Create a public repository on github</span>
					<blockquote>
						<p>Let Github init it + create the <span class="bold">README.md</span> for you</p>
						<p>And just name the repo whatever you want</p>
					</blockquote>
				</li>
				<li><span class="italic">In that repository, make a directory, called</span> <span class="bold italic">00.Enviroment</span>
					<blockquote>
						<p>We will work on that github repository instead of email, for convenient.</p>
						<p>So please let me know the repository name after it's created.</p>
					</blockquote>
				</li>
			</ol>
		</div><!-- END .content -->
	</div><!-- END .part -->
	
	<div class="part">
		<div class="title">
			<h2><span class="underscore">Eclipse</span>, the IDE</h2>
			<p>The recommended IDE. Why? You will answer it yourself, soon</p>
		</div><!-- END .title -->
		<div class="content">
			<h2>The goals</h2>
			<ol>
				<li><span class="italic">Install Eclipse PDT.</span>
					<blockquote>
						<p>You can find it here: <a href="http://www.eclipse.org/pdt/downloads">http://www.eclipse.org/pdt/downloads</a></p>
					</blockquote>
				</li>
				
				<li><span class="italic">Install Emmet for Eclipse</span>
					<blockquote>
						<p>Take a look at its github page <a href="https://github.com/emmetio/emmet-eclipse">https://github.com/emmetio/emmet-eclipse</a></p>
						<p>And the tutorial on its homepage: <a href="http://emmet.io">http://emmet.io</a></p>
					</blockquote>
				</li>
				<li><span class="italic">Install Vrapper for Eclipse</span>
					<blockquote>
						<p>The "how to install" could be found here: <a href="http://vrapper.sourceforge.net/home">http://vrapper.sourceforge.net/home</a></p>
						<p>Just install it, then <span class="bold">do not turn it on</span> yet</p>
					</blockquote>
				</li>
				<li><span class="italic">In the <span class="bold">00.Enviroment</span> (created above), create a Eclipse PHP project</span>
					<blockquote>
						<p>Name the directory whatever you want, of course</p>
						<p>Whithin the project, create 2 files:
							<ul>
								<li class="bold">emmet.html</li>
								<li class="bold">vim.php</li>
							</ul>
						</p>
						<p>Just create $ save them, then leave 'em blank at the moment</p>
					</blockquote>
				</li>
			</ol>
		</div><!-- END .content -->
	</div><!-- END .part -->
